'''Jorge Enrique Rodr<U+00ED>guez Mendieta''' known by his nom de guerre '''Iv<U+00E1>n Vargas''' is a [[Colombia]]n guerrilla leader member of the [[Revolutionary Armed Forces of Colombia]] (FARC-EP), former commander of the [[Middle Magdalena Bloc of the FARC-EP|24th Front]] of the Middle Magdalena Bloc of the FARC-EP. Vargas was arrested in late 2004 by Colombian authorities and extradited to the United States on November 3, 2007 on charges of illegal narcotics trafficking. 

==Early years==

Vargas began his activities with the FARC in 1987 as an aide of the FARC's Secretariat and in 1989 military intelligence of the [[Colombian Army]] reported that Vargas was a guerrilla instructor in the ''Escuala Nacional de Cuadros de las FARC'' (a guerrilla training school of the FARC) in [[Casa Verde]]. In 1991 Vargas was made guerrilla commander of the [[Eastern Bloc of the FARC-EP|22nd Front of the FARC-EP]], part of the Eastern Bloc of that organization.<ref>[http://www.ejercito.mil.co/index.php?idcategoria=34439]</ref>  

==Vietnam training and commander==

The following year, in 1992 Vargas was sent to [[Vietnam]] to receive training in guerrilla tactics. Upon his return he was made commander of the 24th Front of the FARC-EP and commander of the Middle Magdalena region, guerrilla unit that operates in the southern region of [[Bol<U+00ED>var Department]]. <ref>[http://www.ejercito.mil.co/index.php?idcategoria=34439]</ref> 

==Capture and extradition to the United States==

Vargas was extradited to the [[United States]] by the [[Government of Colombia]] charged with conspiracy to export [[illegal drugs]] from Colombia to the United States. In Colombia, the government charged him with rebellion, terrorism, conspiracy to export '''[[illegal drug trade in Colombia|illegal drugs]]'''<ref>[http://www.eltiempo.com/justicia/2007-11-04/ARTICULO-WEB-NOTA_INTERIOR-3801573.html]</ref> According to the United States Attorney General's Office Rodriguez Mendieta allegedly directed the purchase of hundreds of thousands of kilograms of cocaine paste and transmitted billions of Colombian pesos in cocaine proceeds to other FARC officials. Rodriguez Mendieta is also alleged to have ordered the murder of at least eight farmers, including several whom he personally dismembered alive, and to have plotted to retaliate against United States law enforcement officers who were conducting the narcotics-trafficking investigation<ref>[http://www.usdoj.gov/opa/pr/2006/March/06_crm_163.html]</ref>

